"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0731-1462923-olympics-podcast-cruel-defeat-and-the-sweet-science\", \"text\": \"  A deflated Eric Donovan joins Mikey Stafford to discuss a mixed day in the ring for Ireland.  Kellie Harrington's history-making guaranteed bronze was sandwiched between defeats for Jude Gallagher and Aoife O'Rourke.  O'Rourke's defeat was a bit of a shocker but Eric says, while the referee was a little weak, Aoife will be hugely disappointed with how she allowed her Polish opponent, Elzbieta Wojcik, to dictate terms.  Classy Harrington displayed a very different way to win and Eric believes the back-to-back Olympic medallist ranks among ireland's best ever amateur boxers.  Earlier Mikey chatted to Gary Moran ahead of the start of the men's golf tournament, where Shane Lowry and Rory McIlroy must be considered medal hopes.  But, the question has not quite gone away, does golf belong in the Olympics?  Listen to the RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast on theRT\\u00c9 Radio Player,Apple Podcasts,Spotify, orwherever you get your podcasts  We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity. Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"